This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the interaction between the choice of subword merge operations and the model architecture, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of BLEU score as a metric for evaluating the performance of the translation system, which is a common evaluation metric in NLP and machine learning. The paper also discusses the impact of subword merge operations on the language pair, which could be relevant to the subfield of natural language engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Transformer architectures, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) as well as NLP.
